    "narrative": "Today\u2019s optimal lineup for the Austin Waves is anchored by the dual-threat upside of **Kyle Tucker** (76.67) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.91). **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Colin Rea and a wind-out forecast that boosts his long-ball potential, while his 0.372 xwOBA confirms he is primed for a multi-category contribution. **Jackson Merrill** mirrors this output, as his strong platoon advantage against a right-handed starter and prime spot in the three-hole make him a core pillar of our Roto production today. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.40) also earns a high-confidence start; his dynamic platoon edge against Cantillo, combined with a robust 0.384 xwOBA, suggests he could provide the heavy lifting in RBI and runs for the middle of our order.\n\nWe are navigating a few headwinds, most notably the high-skill arms facing **Drake Baldwin** and **Gunnar Henderson**. While **Gunnar Henderson** faces the elite Crochet (2.86 xERA), his massive park factor (+16%) prevents a total benching, and we are counting on his high floor to salvage value. The most difficult personnel decision today was keeping **Coby Mayo** (46.33) on the bench. Despite a solid park factor, the combination of Crochet\u2019s stifling skill set and a lower batting order position forced the optimizer to prioritize the higher-ceiling efficiency of **Andy Pages** (59.97). **Andy Pages** gets the nod primarily due to the wind-out conditions and the specific opportunity to exploit the base-stealing vulnerabilities present in the opposing battery. We will monitor the lineup for **Nasim Nunez**, whose status remains a concern; if he sits, we will have to pivot to a bench reserve to avoid a wasted slot, as his current score (41.38) is already hovering dangerously close to our floor.",
